{meta: title When The Roses Bloom Again}
{meta: artist Johnny Cash}
{meta: writer A.P. Carter}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]In the rattle of the battle came a whisper soft and low
From a soldier who'd been wounded in the [D7]fray
I am [G]dying Captain dying and I pray before I [C]go
You will [D7]give your promise ere I pass [G]away
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Do not ask [C]me dear to linger for I know not what to [G]say
When duty calls your sweetheart's name in [D7]vain
I hope your heart [G]will not be crying if I'm not among the [C]dying
I'll be [D7]with you when the roses bloom [G]again
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Yes when the [C]roses bloom again beside the [G]river
And the robin redbreast sings it's sweet [D7]refrain 
As in days [G]of Old Lang Syne I'll be with you sweetheart [C]mine
I'll be [D7]with you when the roses bloom [G]again
{end_of_verse}

